author: Benedict Correya
text: One of the bigger Anytime Fitness outlets I‚Äôve visited. The gym is spacious with plenty of equipment for both cardio and strength training, so there‚Äôs rarely a wait. Clean and well-maintained, with a comfortable atmosphere that‚Äôs not too crowded ‚Äî great for focused workouts.

text: Adib is awesome! Always greets everyone with a smile and makes the gym such a positive space. Super helpful whenever I need guidance on workouts or equipment, you can tell they really care about the members here!

author: nikko jenkins
text:
Poor management. Rude and doesn't care about their members. One of the staff in particular, adib was very impolite and showed attitude towards me. Though i understand perhaps adib might not be the brightest kid, it was very unprofessional of
him to do so. Then again, it's bukit batok csc. Heard numerous problems about them. Many came and many left. I see why now. Renu (manager) and her clowns!

author: Easter
text: The facilities here are clean, the staff are amiable and friendly. They even provide snacks for their members sometimes! The air conditioning here is also pretty strong which is a huge plus considering quite a few afs have weak air conditioning.

text: Very hard to find entrance and coming at night I find the gym poorly lit. But it‚Äôs clean, spacious and has all the equipment I needed.

The best AF outlet one can ask for. This gym is really well equipped, spacious and has a great vibe. Friendly staff, especially the manager and the 2 wonderful ladies at the reception. The gym is well maintained by the custodian who is always full of smiles & welcoming.

A huge shout out to the fantastic team which made this place a gem in the west.

author: Deepa Suppiah
text: Had a great experience and the staff are very friendly. They ensured that we felt comfortable in joining anytime fitness and they were not pushy at all.

author: Khairulanwar bin azmi

author: Muhamad Firdaus Yusof
text:
Gym Review

I‚Äôve had an amazing experience at this gym! The staff is incredibly friendly and professional, always ready to help with any questions or offer guidance. The space is impressively wide and open, making it comfortable to work out without feeling crowded.

They‚Äôve done a fantastic job ensuring there‚Äôs plenty of equipment available, so you‚Äôre never stuck waiting for your turn. Whether it‚Äôs cardio machines, weights, or specialty gear, they‚Äôve got it all.

One of the standout features for me is the availability of clean and well-maintained toilets and showers. It‚Äôs a huge plus, especially if you‚Äôre working out before or after work and need to freshen up.

Overall, this gym strikes the perfect balance of professionalism, comfort, and functionality. Highly recommend it!

author: Fairoz
text:
Came here to check out the newly refurbished gym. Unfortunately, whilst on the pec deck machine, a staff member approached me to say that I cannot continue working out since I have my crocs shoes on even though my toes were covered. Was told to finish up my last set even though I asked if I could at least finish my workout for the day.
Gotta respect the rules. üòï
Do make sure you are properly attired to workout in this gym. Otherwise the gym is clean and tidy.

author: Troven Seth
text: Stuff very friendly , at times even provide fruits for energy !!! Great place to gym as it‚Äôs spacious

a very clean and spacious outlet with dim lights! has every equipment that i need to target the muscle group i‚Äôm trying to hit!

one of my fav outlets

author: Aisyah Yazaid

The newly renovated gym looks incredible‚Äîbeautiful lighting and super spacious! Coach Kesh is an amazing and friendly personal trainer who has been a huge help in my fitness journey!! His personalized workout plans are perfectly challenging, and I always look forward to our sessions. Each visit leaves me feeling euphoric and motivated!

100% recommend this gym for its fantastic environment, excellent amenities, and lovely people!

author: Freddy Seah
text: This is the best AF gym I have been to.  Loved the lighting and equipment setup.  Great view for those on the treadmill.

author: nick ong

author: Tiger Chang
text:
Club is great and clean.

BUT such a Fantastic experience to cancel the membership.

30days notice period is 1st day from next month. Not from the day requested. Agreement stated 30 days notice period, WA message stated 30days notice period. When come to email, it become 1st day of next month. Message to check, twist again, base on the date signed on the paperwork.

Have to pay for the full membership fee for the coming month till i requested to meet the person in charge then became prorated.

It's no about the fee, is it about how your team handle a customer request.
Ps, Person in Charge was busy, not able to meet even special requested during staff hour or when she will be in the outlet.

author: Ken Lim
text:
Management can't resolve membership issue (in fact I'm asking for online payment options to pay my dues) for close to 6months but keep asking me for membership renewal instead. I'm the one chasing them so I can make payment!!

Strongly don't recommend this management team. Communication with the team is futile. Worst experience with any gym establishment by far.

p.s the issue was resolved by club manager within the day(few hours) after the google review was posted.

It's way better and friendlier there. They handle admin work way better than these sleazy bunch in bukit batok CSC.

author: Vincent Lian
text: The gym is clean and tidy. Since it's newly opened all equipments are new and in excellent condition. The functional area is about 100m¬≤. There's a pretty decent shower facility and lockers are provided. Even hairdryers and cologne is available so don't you worry that your hair is not gonna dry lol. I'd say it has almost all the equipments and machine you'll need for a simple to hardcore workout. Give the airbike a try if you wanna push to your maximum heart rate lol. Took me quite a while to steady my heart rate after a short explosive session. I came in midnight so it's empty, not sure about the human traffic during the day. Music volume is just nice, not too loud but not too soft either (those gyms with music too soft can be a little annoying sometimes) There are classes such as zumba and yoga available too on the weekdays(not sure about the weekends). Overall it's a great place to work out. (probably coz I was the only one there haha)

author: Saaim Shoaib
text: Amazing gym with showers, couches, WiFi, great equipment in amazing condition, lots of space to do floor and boxing, lots of machines and weights as well as air conditioning and 24/7 access to over 2,000 gyms! But is a little expensive for the key but is definitely worth every penny if you go regularly.

author: Akhilesh Porwal
text: Gym is spacious. And place is nice. It feels good when you go to gym. Early morning gym is almost vacant. Only issue is that most of the time weight plates are not racked.

author: Kamaliyah Majeed
text: I have been training with my PT Muneer for the past 3 months. Doctor has advised that my cholesterol was high and I needed to do strength training. Muneer has been so caring and had planned amazing workout sessions for me to improve my health. Had my blood test redone and my cholesterol levels have improved alot. Highly recommend Muneer as a PT

author: Daniel Chang
text:
Horrible Covid19 management. Literally almost all surrounding ANYTIME fitness outlets are opened already 24 hours for months (as should be in it name) and this outlet refuses to live up to its name. As someone who works an 8am-6pm job, I cannot gym in the morning now because the earliest the gym opens is 7am. I'm left with the choice to gym at horribly crowded after work hours with little energy that I have left after work. Please sign up for other gym memberships nearby like gymmboxx at Jcube that has reduced crowd (based on google), lower cost and opens much earlier (closes much later too). To make the situation worse, equipment in the gym has been massively reduced. Customers bear all this and still pay the same gym membership rate. Absolutely unacceptable.
FYI: Members are already complaining on their social media platforms and nothing is done. Due to Covid19 in the early phases, their previous operating hours were 6am-12am now they open as late as 8am on weekends and close as early as 10pm.

author: Debbie S.
text: Horrible customer service. The manager did not allow me to freeze and terminate my membership at the same time and charged my credit card for the notice period without my consent. Would never go back no matter how much they boast on how many outlets they have.

author: rif
text:
Gym manager refused to get the staff to apologise to me after

1) shouting at me when i was using the toilet. switched off the toilet light and got someone to bang the toilet door for me to get out (i was barely 5 minutes in). back then, there was no signage that says it is restricted for public use. left a google review and the manager asked me to remove the review despite review being factual.

2) staff were talking bad about me after that first incident (happened a year ago). i knew this from one a staff named Adib. which brings to the next point.

3) Adib engaged with me via Whatsapp text to tell me that i was charged extra for invalid payment as i changed my card. so, i asked him a simple question, why is there no notice for invalid payment because i dont want to get charged extra. and Adib handled my query with no grace and full of snob. He even made snarky remarks to me and encouraged me to look at the procedure to quit AF even after years of being a patron there.

4) told the manager about this through email. however, manager refused to get the staff involved to apologise to me and he was being rather dismissive towards the issue.

put this matter up online and apparently a lot of people thinks the service from the staff of AF CSC is horrible too.

author: Leonel Lim
text:
Dear Cuddles,

Thank you for taking the time to share your feedback about your experience with Anytime Fitness Bukit Batok. We apologize that we fell short of your expectations.

Can you please contact us directly so we can learn more about your visit and make things right? Your satisfaction is our top priority, and we value your feedback.

Best regards,
AF Bukit Batok Management
